          correct: 1, 
          sol: "<b>Step 1: Initial Tension</b><br>In air, the tension supports the full weight of the object. Specific gravity \\( \\rho \\) means its density is \\( \\rho \\cdot \\rho_w \\).<br>Weight \\( W = V (\\rho \\cdot \\rho_w) g \\). So initially, \\( T = V \\rho \\rho_w g \\).<br><br><b>Step 2: Calculate Buoyant Force</b><br>When half submerged, the displaced volume of water is \\( V/2 \\).<br>Buoyant force \\( B = \\left(\\frac{V}{2}\\right) \\rho_w g \\).<br><br><b>Step 3: Final Tension</b><br>The new tension is \\( T' = W - B = V \\rho \\rho_w g - \\frac{V}{2} \\rho_w g \\).<br>Substitute \\( V \\rho_w g = \\frac{T}{\\rho} \\):<br>\\( T' = T - \\frac{1}{2} \\left(\\frac{T}{\\rho}\\right) = T \\left(1 - \\frac{1}{2\\rho}\\right) = T \\left(\\frac{2\\rho - 1}{2\\rho}\\right) \\)."
